"[{\"comment\": \"Aggrostone Cancer of Aggrocraft\", \"commentId\": \"38064\", \"commentDate\": \"1495807753\"}, {\"comment\": \"stop playing ladder decks in casual then\", \"commentId\": \"38065\", \"commentDate\": \"1495807817\"}, {\"comment\": \"concede and look for different opponent\", \"commentId\": \"38066\", \"commentDate\": \"1495808344\"}, {\"comment\": \"taking 23 damage in 4 turns is extremely fair and balanced   in casual  my fault for not playing around it\", \"commentId\": \"38067\", \"commentDate\": \"1495808984\"}, {\"comment\": \"Thats not how probability works  If the matches are independent events  the probability for facing pirate warrior should be same each time  However  I highly doubt that Blizzards match matching isnt skewed in some way\", \"commentId\": \"38068\", \"commentDate\": \"1495809171\"}, {\"comment\": \"This game is trying to make me quit  And you bet its fing effective  Play 10 games of each midrange shaman  mage and palading  Lose by turn 5  Play 10 games of each aggro pirate warrior  druid  murloc paladin and hunter  Opponent always clear my board  Ungoro supposed to make things better but I only see it make things worse  Before Ungoro release  control match up still has chance with Reno Jackson  Now you lose board mean you fing lose the game  Why bother to play a game where I spend thousands dollar just to make myself worse  And none of the money spend has ROI value  I spend and make myself salty  No F thanks Blizzard\", \"commentId\": \"38069\", \"commentDate\": \"1495809670\"}, {\"comment\": \"Had full board control with big minions with the spirit walker deathrattle buff  But I ended up losing because I didnt play around mind control    My opponent was a mage  He stole my Primordial Drake  which then gave him another\", \"commentId\": \"38070\", \"commentDate\": \"1495809689\"}, {\"comment\": \"Thats why i dont play constructed anymore  Random random random random random\", \"commentId\": \"38071\", \"commentDate\": \"14958